                When your washer fails to drain, it could be due to a clogged
                drain hose or pump. Small items like socks can sometimes block
                the drainage system. To fix this, first check and clean the
                drain hose and pump. If these parts are broken, you'll need to
                replace them. Regularly cleaning the machine and avoiding
                overloading it can help prevent this issue. If draining problems
                continue, a professional washer repair might be needed.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
