                source, a broken start switch, or issues with the control board.
                First, check if the machine is plugged in and that the outlet is
                working. If the start switch is not engaging, it may need
                replacing. A quick reset of the machine can sometimes fix minor
                glitches. If the control board is the issue, it might be worth
                getting a professional washer repair. Always choose to consult
                the user manual for specific troubleshooting steps.
