                The agitator or impeller is the part inside the drum that moves
                the clothes around for effective cleaning. If your clothes
                aren’t getting clean, this part might need some attention.
                Different washing machine models use either an agitator or an
                impeller, each with its pros and cons. Repair can involve
                replacing worn-out parts or adjusting the existing ones. Watch
                for signs of wear, such as broken fins or unusual noises.
                Regular cleaning can extend the life of these components. If
                you’re considering buying a new machine, think about whether you
                prefer an agitator or impeller model.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
