              <p>
                The water inlet valve controls the flow of water into the
                washing machine. If the washer isn’t filling correctly, this
                valve might need a quick repair. Over time, mineral deposits can
                clog the valve, reducing water flow. Most models have easily
                accessible valves that can be cleaned or replaced. If you find
                inconsistent water levels, it’s likely a valve issue. Regularly
                checking and cleaning the valve can prevent bigger problems.
                Always close the water supply before attempting any repairs.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Door Lock:</h3>
              <p>
