              <h2>
                What is included in Washing Machine maintenance and how it can
                help prevent repairs
              </h2>
            </div>
            <div class="content__page-hed-desc"></div>
          </div>

          <div class="content__page-full-desc content__page-full-desc-ph-ri">
            <div class="content__page-desc-phot">
              <img
                src="/washer-repair/washer5.webp"
                width="400px"
                height="500px"
                alt="Microwave Repair"
                loading="lazy"
              />
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <p>
                Regular washing machine maintenance can help extend the lifespan
                of your appliance, improve its efficiency, and prevent costly
                repairs. Here’s a detailed list of what is typically included in
                washing machine maintenance and how it helps:
              </p>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <h3>Cleaning the Drum:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Run an empty wash cycle with a
                      washing machine cleaner or a mixture of vinegar and baking
                      soda.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Removes buildup of detergent, fabric
                      softener, and mineral deposits, preventing odor and
                      ensuring the drum functions efficiently.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Inspecting and Cleaning the Door Seal:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Wipe down the door seal (gasket)
                      regularly to remove lint, detergent residue, and moisture.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Prevents mold, mildew, and bacteria
                      buildup, which can cause odors and damage the seal.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Cleaning the Detergent Dispenser:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Remove and clean the detergent
                      and fabric softener dispensers regularly.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Prevents clogging and ensures that
                      detergent and softener are dispensed correctly.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Checking and Cleaning the Filter:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Locate and clean the washing
                      machine filter to remove lint, coins, and other debris.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Ensures proper draining and prevents
                      blockages that can cause water damage and inefficient
                      operation.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Inspecting Hoses:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Check water inlet and drain hoses
                      for signs of wear, leaks, or cracks.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Prevents leaks that can lead to water
                      damage and ensures efficient water flow.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Balancing the Machine:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Ensure the washing machine is
                      level and adjust the feet if necessary.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Prevents excessive vibration and
                      noise, reducing wear on internal components.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Running Hot Water Before Starting a Cycle:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Run hot water in the sink closest
                      to your washing machine before starting a cycle.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Ensures the washing machine starts
                      with hot water, improving cleaning efficiency.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Using the Right Detergent:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Use the appropriate type and
                      amount of detergent for your machine (HE detergent for
                      high-efficiency washers).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Prevents excessive suds that can lead
                      to buildup and ensures efficient cleaning.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Avoiding Overloading:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Do not overload the washing
                      machine with clothes.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Ensures clothes are cleaned properly
                      and reduces strain on the motor and drum.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Checking the Water Inlet Valve:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Inspect the water inlet valve for
                      signs of clogging or damage.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Ensures proper water flow into the
                      machine, preventing filling issues.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Wiping Down the Exterior:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Regularly clean the exterior of
                      the washing machine with a damp cloth.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Keeps the machine looking new and
                      prevents dust and dirt from entering the internal
                      components.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Monitoring Performance:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Pay attention to any changes in
                      performance, such as unusual noises, vibrations, or error
                      codes.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Early detection of issues can prevent
                      more serious problems and costly repairs.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Ensuring Proper Ventilation:</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Ensure there is adequate space
                      around the washing machine for ventilation.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Prevents overheating and ensures
                      efficient operation.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>

                <li>
                  <h3>Cleaning the Lint Trap (if applicable):</h3>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <b>What It Involves: </b>Clean the lint trap (if your
                      model has one) after every load.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>How It Helps: </b>Prevents lint buildup that can lead
                      to clogs and inefficient operation.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ol>

              <p>
                By incorporating these maintenance tasks into your routine, you
                can help prevent many common washing machine problems, ensuring
                your appliance runs efficiently and effectively for years to
                come. Regular maintenance not only saves money on repairs but
                also improves the overall performance and longevity of your
                washing machine.
              </p>
            </div>
